WEBVTT

00:13.000 --> 00:15.416
(MUSIC PLAYING)

00:20.875 --> 00:24.750
MAN: (SINGING)
It was Christmas Eve, babe

00:25.958 --> 00:29.416
In the drunk tank

00:29.750 --> 00:32.958
An old man said to me

00:33.708 --> 00:37.083
Won't see another one

00:38.083 --> 00:42.375
And then we sang a song

00:42.875 --> 00:46.750
The Rare Old Mountain's Dew

00:46.833 --> 00:50.000
I turned my face away

00:51.000 --> 00:55.083
And dreamed about you...

00:55.625 --> 00:59.041
(LAUGHING)

01:03.000 --> 01:04.083
Hey, this one looks good.

01:05.291 --> 01:08.625
What in the fires of Ogord
y'all think you doing?

01:08.708 --> 01:12.000
Hey, Captain. We're just, uh...
Have you ever heard of Christmas?

01:12.083 --> 01:13.083
What?

01:13.166 --> 01:16.208
Well, it's a celebration we have
once a year on Earth,

01:16.916 --> 01:19.625
where everybody gets presents
for each other.

01:20.458 --> 01:23.666
So, me and Kraglin made this tree
and we got gifts for everyone.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.000
It was Pete's idea.

01:25.458 --> 01:26.875
Eh...

01:26.958 --> 01:31.333
-And this one here's for you.
-Don't come at me with no damn gifts.

01:31.500 --> 01:35.958
What a Ravager gets, he works for.
We ain't about no damn handouts.

01:36.541 --> 01:41.166
-It's more like a sign of appreciation.
-That sounds more like sentiment, boy.

01:41.250 --> 01:43.833
That may be okay for you
mushy types on Terra,

01:44.125 --> 01:47.166
but out here in the cold rigors of space,
it's what'll get you killed.

01:47.833 --> 01:50.375
And you, you ought to know better.

01:51.458 --> 01:54.708
Now, get this crap out of here.

01:54.833 --> 01:56.666
If it ain't out of here before I get back,

01:56.750 --> 02:00.708
you're both gonna be cleaning the latrines
for the rest of the damn year.

02:00.958 --> 02:04.750
-But that's Gef's favorite job.
-You talking back now, Kraglin?

02:04.833 --> 02:05.833
No.

02:06.791 --> 02:08.375
(YELLING ANGRILY)

02:10.333 --> 02:13.083
I hate Christmas!

02:18.250 --> 02:22.125
And that's how
Yondu ruined Christmas forever.

02:22.333 --> 02:24.083
That is so sad.

02:24.208 --> 02:25.875
(LAUGHS)

02:25.958 --> 02:28.083
I like the part where Yondu
kicked over the tree.

02:28.208 --> 02:29.416
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)

02:35.041 --> 02:37.000
Anyways, I just saw on the Multi-calendar

02:37.083 --> 02:40.166
that right now on Earth,
it's almost Christmastime.

02:40.250 --> 02:43.291
So, yeah, it kind of brings back
some memories.

02:43.375 --> 02:44.500
Yondu had a point.

02:44.625 --> 02:46.583
Ever since buying Knowhere
from The Collector,

02:46.750 --> 02:49.666
we don't have time for trivialities
like Christmas.

02:50.208 --> 02:53.083
This place needs a lot of fixing up
before it's livable.

02:53.708 --> 02:56.541
-Yeah, I reckon we've got work to do.
-Yeah.

03:00.833 --> 03:02.833
That was such a heartbreaking story.

03:03.125 --> 03:06.166
I know. I hate stories
where everybody lives.

03:15.625 --> 03:16.875
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

03:21.333 --> 03:24.541
Cosmo, what use is telekinesis
if you can't even aim?

03:24.708 --> 03:26.666
COSMO: You wanna do it? Do it.

03:27.375 --> 03:29.750
Just concentrate, you stupid mutt.

03:30.250 --> 03:31.500
(BARKS)

03:32.916 --> 03:33.916
What?

03:34.083 --> 03:36.541
COSMO: I refuse to do any more work
while you demean me.

03:36.666 --> 03:39.708
All right, all right.
I'm sorry. Chill out.

03:39.833 --> 03:43.208
COSMO: Also, I want one of those
delicious treats in that bag.

03:44.375 --> 03:46.125
(ROCKET GROANS)

03:46.333 --> 03:47.791
(BARKS)

03:48.750 --> 03:50.166
(COSMO GIGGLES)

03:51.916 --> 03:53.791
ROCKET: All right, that's it.
Back to work.

03:57.583 --> 03:58.833
BZERMIKITOKOLOK: Here he comes.

04:00.500 --> 04:01.500
Hey, Peter.

04:02.500 --> 04:04.416
Oh. Hi, Bzermikitokolok.

04:04.583 --> 04:06.375
My bandmates and I have been mastering

04:06.458 --> 04:09.458
these old Earth instruments
and working on a little ditty.

04:09.541 --> 04:11.333
And I thought you might
be able to help us out

04:11.416 --> 04:13.625
as it's about
one of your Earth traditions.

04:13.916 --> 04:15.416
-Oh?
-Christmas.

04:15.708 --> 04:16.708
Oh.

04:16.791 --> 04:19.750
Everything I know about Christmas,
I learned from Rocket,

04:19.833 --> 04:22.458
who learned from Cosmo,
who learned from Kraglin,

04:22.583 --> 04:23.708
who learned from you.

04:23.791 --> 04:25.708
So I thought I might just take it back
to the source

04:25.791 --> 04:28.333
and make sure
I understand this all correctly.

04:28.458 --> 04:30.875
This is, after all, a historical document.

04:31.083 --> 04:32.250
-Okay. Yeah, sure.
-Okay.

04:32.375 --> 04:34.958
(SINGING) Out on the third planet
closest to the sun

04:35.041 --> 04:38.916
There's a special celebration
And it sounds quite fun

04:39.041 --> 04:41.958
A jolly old fellow brings toys to everyone

04:42.041 --> 04:44.958
On a holiday they call Christmas

04:45.041 --> 04:46.791
That's perfect. Good. Bzer, good job.

04:46.875 --> 04:48.333
Now I'm not gonna lie

04:48.458 --> 04:49.458
Oh, there's more.

04:49.583 --> 04:50.833
It makes no sense to me

04:51.041 --> 04:56.333
But here's what I've discovered
about this Christmas mystery

04:56.416 --> 04:58.875
I'm super busy. Is this a long song?

04:59.208 --> 05:00.416
One, two, three.

05:00.625 --> 05:05.958
Santa is a furry freak
with epic superpowers

05:06.250 --> 05:12.000
He flies to every human home
in under 14 hours

05:12.416 --> 05:14.583
He's a master burglar

05:14.666 --> 05:15.666
No.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.500
A pro at picking locks

05:17.583 --> 05:18.583
No.

05:18.666 --> 05:20.833
If you don't leave milk and cookies out

05:21.333 --> 05:24.458
He will put dung in your socks

05:24.541 --> 05:26.750
That is not part of the lore at all.

05:27.041 --> 05:29.750
If you act nicely through the night

05:29.875 --> 05:32.583
And don't jump on your bed

05:33.208 --> 05:38.458
Santa comes with sugar plums
and hurls them at your head

05:38.958 --> 05:41.625
But if you're on his naughty list

05:41.708 --> 05:44.500
He shoots missiles at your toes

05:44.833 --> 05:47.208
He might just roast your chestnuts

05:47.291 --> 05:52.041
With his powerful flamethrower

05:52.125 --> 05:54.083
No, he doesn't have a flamethrower.

05:54.291 --> 05:55.833
Rein, rein, rein, rein, rein

05:55.916 --> 05:56.916
That's kinda cool.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.208
Deer, deer, deer, deer, deer

05:59.708 --> 06:05.208
I don't know what Christmas is
But Christmastime is here

06:07.250 --> 06:11.791
He's compelled his creepy elves
to do his every wish

06:11.875 --> 06:12.916
Huh?

06:13.000 --> 06:18.416
One sought to be a dentist
Now he's sleeping with the fish

06:19.166 --> 06:24.541
Mrs. Claus, she works the pole
Plans her man's demise

06:24.625 --> 06:25.625
No!

06:25.708 --> 06:27.583
Soon the elves will all rise up

06:27.666 --> 06:31.125
And stab out Santa's eyes

06:31.333 --> 06:32.791
I am Groot.

06:33.958 --> 06:36.125
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho

06:36.875 --> 06:39.291
Earthlings are so weird

06:39.375 --> 06:40.416
That's true.

06:40.500 --> 06:45.083
I don't know what Christmas is
But Christmastime is here

06:45.833 --> 06:48.083
Ho, ho, ho, ho, ho

06:48.750 --> 06:51.500
Earthlings are so weird

06:51.750 --> 06:57.333
I don't know what Christmas is
But Christmastime is here

06:57.875 --> 07:00.916
What the heck's a turtledove?

07:01.750 --> 07:05.041
And who lit up that deer?

07:06.916 --> 07:12.708
I don't know what Christmas is
But Christmastime is here

07:12.791 --> 07:18.333
I don't know what Christmas is
But Christmastime is here

07:19.000 --> 07:23.000
Or maybe it's there
Or it's somewhere

07:23.666 --> 07:24.750
I don't know.

07:27.125 --> 07:30.166
-You just got these instruments?
-Thank you, Knowhere.

07:30.250 --> 07:31.708
(CROWD APPLAUDING TEPIDLY)

07:33.250 --> 07:34.958
Have you ever seen a crowd more into it?

07:37.791 --> 07:39.750
He loved it, guys. (SIGHS IN RELIEF)

07:42.708 --> 07:45.000
It sounds like Christmas
is a wonderful time,

07:45.125 --> 07:46.916
and Yondu ruined it for Peter.

07:47.666 --> 07:49.458
I feel like I should do something.

07:49.666 --> 07:54.000
-Why?
-Because of, you know, my secret.

07:54.625 --> 07:56.083
The one only you know.

07:56.208 --> 07:58.541
That you ate the entire bowl of zarg-nuts
in the commissary?

07:58.625 --> 08:00.833
-My other secret.
-That you're Quill's sister?

08:02.375 --> 08:04.083
Why don't you just tell people the truth?

08:04.375 --> 08:09.291
Peter's father, our father,
killed his mother and tried to kill him.

08:10.541 --> 08:13.583
I don't want him to be reminded of that
every time he sees me.

08:13.666 --> 08:15.541
No, I meant about the zarg-nuts.

08:15.666 --> 08:18.166
Oh. I don't think anyone cares
about that but you.

08:19.000 --> 08:20.333
Maybe because I'm his sister,

08:20.416 --> 08:23.083
I feel like I should give Peter
a happy Christmas.

08:23.375 --> 08:25.916
He's so sad about Gamora being gone.

08:27.083 --> 08:30.541
Maybe if we gave Peter
a really wonderful Christmas gift,

08:30.708 --> 08:31.833
it would make him happy.

08:31.916 --> 08:34.666
Well, we could give him those zarg-nuts,
except you ate them all.

08:34.875 --> 08:36.541
Get over the zarg-nuts!

08:39.166 --> 08:43.083
-What kind of present?
-Something special he will never forget.

08:44.500 --> 08:48.041
-What about someone special?
-What?

08:48.125 --> 08:51.041
Over the years, Quill has talked about
one person more than any other.

08:51.291 --> 08:53.791
A legendary hero
who has saved countless lives.

08:54.041 --> 08:56.458
We could give him to Quill as a present.

08:58.041 --> 08:59.583
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ON RADIO)

09:00.541 --> 09:01.750
-(CAR DOOR SHUTS)
-(MUSIC STOPS)

09:01.833 --> 09:04.000
(PHONE RINGING)

09:05.916 --> 09:07.541
Kyra, hey, honey.

09:07.625 --> 09:08.666
-KYRA: Hey, baby.
-(CHUCKLES)

09:08.750 --> 09:11.041
I can't wait for you guys
to get back from New York.

09:11.125 --> 09:12.375
-Did you get the stuff?
-Yep.

09:12.458 --> 09:13.833
Yeah, I got all the presents.

09:14.458 --> 09:18.166
Everything is set
for the perfect family Christmas.

09:20.041 --> 09:21.208
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

09:25.666 --> 09:28.041
MAN: (SINGING)
I don't care what the neighbors say

09:28.250 --> 09:30.708
Christmastime is near

09:31.375 --> 09:34.208
I don't care what anyone says

09:34.291 --> 09:36.958
Christmas is full of cheer

09:37.041 --> 09:38.583
All I know is that Santa's...

09:38.666 --> 09:40.000
Wow!

09:42.750 --> 09:45.458
I wonder which one belongs to Kevin Bacon.

09:48.625 --> 09:50.708
(SOBBING)

09:53.375 --> 09:56.166
Drax, why are they staring?

09:57.333 --> 10:00.375
You put the cloaking device on
like you said you did, right?

10:00.458 --> 10:01.500
Yes.

10:06.250 --> 10:09.500
I can plainly see that you just did it
right now in front of me.

10:09.625 --> 10:10.916
-No, I didn't.
-Yes, you did.

10:11.000 --> 10:12.000
No, I didn't.

10:13.500 --> 10:15.166
I wish I brought Groot.

10:16.708 --> 10:20.833
So, we'll go down into the city
and ask people where Kevin Bacon is.

10:20.916 --> 10:23.000
DRAX: Do you think
Kevin Bacon is the leader of the world

10:23.083 --> 10:24.916
or just to most people?

10:25.541 --> 10:28.791
-I think everybody.
-Oh! I'm so excited.

10:29.916 --> 10:31.875
(BOTH LAUGH GLEEFULLY)

10:32.541 --> 10:36.750
MAN: (SINGING) I can hear the sleigh bells
coming around the bend

10:36.833 --> 10:39.583
Here comes the darkest end

10:39.666 --> 10:41.583
Christmas is here

10:43.333 --> 10:44.833
(GASPS) Look.

10:46.583 --> 10:48.791
(GIGGLING EXCITEDLY)

10:53.500 --> 10:54.500
(WOMAN EXCLAIMS)

10:58.208 --> 10:59.791
Steve!

11:03.958 --> 11:06.208
-Why is he running away?
-I don't know.

11:09.958 --> 11:14.250
-Hey!
-No! I'm sorry. GoBots killed his cousin.

11:14.333 --> 11:17.875
-I'll rip your head off!
-Drax! Stop being a bigot.

11:20.583 --> 11:21.625
(BELL DINGING)

11:21.708 --> 11:24.916
Oh. Hey, can we get a picture?
Come on, guys. Come on. Ready?

11:26.125 --> 11:27.416
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

11:27.500 --> 11:30.083
-Okay, amazing. Thank you so much.
-Thank you.

11:30.166 --> 11:32.166
We got a picture with the God of War.

11:36.041 --> 11:38.166
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

11:38.541 --> 11:40.958
(CROWD CHEERING AND WHOOPING)

11:43.375 --> 11:45.666
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

11:47.125 --> 11:48.916
(WOMEN LAUGHING)

11:49.916 --> 11:52.375
My dear

11:52.541 --> 11:55.500
Is this Christmas?

11:55.583 --> 12:01.000
Whatever happened to that festive cheer?

12:01.083 --> 12:02.875
(LAUGHING)

12:02.958 --> 12:04.625
(DRAX GRUNTING)

12:17.708 --> 12:19.916
MANTIS: Could Kevin Bacon be in here?

12:20.000 --> 12:22.375
WOMAN: (SINGING)
Don't think I have the energy

12:22.625 --> 12:24.833
To add to my already mad rush

12:24.916 --> 12:26.583
-(MUSIC CONTINUES)
-(CROWD CLAMORING)

12:26.666 --> 12:28.500
The perfect gift for me would be

12:28.583 --> 12:30.541
Completions and connections left from

12:30.625 --> 12:32.791
Last year, ski shop

12:32.875 --> 12:34.875
Encounter, most interesting

12:34.958 --> 12:36.916
Had his number but never the time

12:37.000 --> 12:38.666
Most of '81 passed along those lines

12:38.750 --> 12:41.208
So deck those halls
Trim those trees

12:41.291 --> 12:43.208
Raise up cups of Christmas cheer

12:43.291 --> 12:45.666
I just need to catch my breath

12:45.750 --> 12:47.583
Give us your finest libations.

12:48.541 --> 12:50.791
Have you seen Kevin Bacon anywhere?

12:50.875 --> 12:53.125
Why would I know where
Kevin Bacon is located?

12:55.291 --> 12:57.375
Calendar picture, frozen landscape

12:57.458 --> 12:59.333
Chilled this room for 24 days

12:59.416 --> 13:01.791
Evergreens, sparkling snow

13:01.875 --> 13:03.125
(HISSING)

13:10.458 --> 13:11.916
Mmm. More.

13:15.500 --> 13:17.416
(MANTIS GIGGLES)

13:18.500 --> 13:19.958
(MANTIS WHOOPS)

13:22.291 --> 13:27.041
-Come out and dance with us.
-Dancing is for people who are pathetic.

13:27.166 --> 13:28.750
(CHUCKLES)

13:29.291 --> 13:31.125
-Well, how about a drink then?
-Yes!

13:31.375 --> 13:33.041
Two shots of tequila, please.

13:33.125 --> 13:35.666
-(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)
-(MANTIS LAUGHS WILDLY)

13:37.041 --> 13:38.791
(LAUGHING HEARTILY)

13:43.791 --> 13:45.666
(LAUGHING)

13:47.208 --> 13:49.000
-(WHOOPING)
-(LAUGHING)

13:52.625 --> 13:55.208
I can't believe not a single one

13:55.291 --> 13:59.791
of our new homies (HICCUPS)
know where Kevin Bacon is.

14:00.208 --> 14:04.000
There are tens of thousands of people
on this planet

14:04.875 --> 14:08.000
and we don't even know
what Kevin Bacon looks like.

14:08.083 --> 14:09.541
MAN: (SINGING)
Said it was like Christmas

14:09.625 --> 14:11.208
You wanna know where Kevin Bacon lives?

14:13.666 --> 14:14.708
Yes.

14:23.541 --> 14:24.791
That's 40 bucks.

14:28.125 --> 14:29.166
Uh-oh.

14:33.916 --> 14:36.125
I don't know where my money is.

14:37.875 --> 14:39.500
Give it to me for free.

14:39.583 --> 14:42.000
By the time we got to Oslo

14:43.708 --> 14:45.208
Give me all your money.

14:45.333 --> 14:46.958
The snow was gone

14:47.958 --> 14:50.250
MANTIS: Drax, move faster.

14:52.083 --> 14:55.083
MAN 1 ON TV: It won't be exactly the same
as the one you have on Earth,

14:55.166 --> 14:57.000
but I'm sure it will serve your purpose.

14:57.083 --> 15:00.250
MAN 2: Good. Good.
Now I'd like to get going

15:00.333 --> 15:03.333
and have the toy shop operating full-blast

15:03.416 --> 15:06.250
so that I can return
to Earth for Christmas.

15:06.333 --> 15:11.250
'Cause, you know, Mrs. Claus
is a very good-natured woman. But...

15:11.333 --> 15:14.625
Santa Claus,
you will never return to Earth.

15:14.708 --> 15:15.708
Wait.

15:15.791 --> 15:17.291
(LAUGHING)

15:18.166 --> 15:19.791
(DOORBELL RINGS)

15:24.541 --> 15:25.666
KEVIN: Yeah. Can I help you?

15:25.750 --> 15:27.125
(GASPS)

15:27.458 --> 15:31.125
Yes. We are looking for
the legendary Kevin Bacon.

15:31.208 --> 15:33.666
We're looking for
the legendary Kevin Bacon.

15:33.875 --> 15:34.916
I just said that, Drax.

15:35.000 --> 15:37.291
Your voice is small and mousy.
I think maybe he didn't hear you.

15:37.416 --> 15:40.416
He heard. He's Kevin Bacon.
He's probably got great ears.

15:40.500 --> 15:43.083
I'm sorry, guys. I can't help you.

15:43.583 --> 15:44.916
But wait, wait, wait, wait.

15:46.750 --> 15:48.541
-(RINGS DOORBELL)
-Hello?

15:49.958 --> 15:50.958
-(RINGS DOORBELL)
-Hello?

15:52.333 --> 15:54.833
-(RINGS DOORBELL CONTINUOUSLY)
-Hello? Hello? Hello!

16:00.166 --> 16:03.625
He's gone. Look what you did.

16:04.000 --> 16:07.541
You acted weird
and you made him not want to talk to us.

16:08.000 --> 16:09.000
Sorry.

16:13.958 --> 16:16.458
Do you think you can toss me
over the gate if you...

16:16.541 --> 16:18.333
(MANTIS EXCLAIMS)

16:19.791 --> 16:22.083
Ow! (GRUNTS)

16:22.666 --> 16:25.833
-What are you doing?
-Tossing you over the gate.

16:26.583 --> 16:30.416
I didn't mean right that second.
I meant after I was ready.

16:31.000 --> 16:32.833
I wasn't even done talking.

16:32.916 --> 16:34.916
Toss you over the gate.
Don't toss you over the gate.

16:35.000 --> 16:36.041
Make up your mind.

16:49.458 --> 16:50.666
Whoa!

16:51.083 --> 16:52.458
(GASPS)

16:55.125 --> 16:58.791
-I want this funny man.
-Don't just take stuff.

16:59.583 --> 17:01.250
(GASPS)

17:01.333 --> 17:02.333
Oh.

17:03.750 --> 17:06.083
But I guess that's what it's here for.

17:08.041 --> 17:10.666
-(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ON TV)
-(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

17:10.750 --> 17:12.666
MANTIS: Kevin Bacon!

17:14.708 --> 17:16.458
Kevin Bacon!

17:17.958 --> 17:19.750
Kevin Bacon!

17:20.291 --> 17:21.791
(DOORBELL RINGS)

17:22.333 --> 17:23.875
(BANGING ON DOOR)

17:24.333 --> 17:25.750
Kevin Bacon!

17:27.000 --> 17:28.458
Kevin Bacon!

17:28.541 --> 17:31.375
(DOORBELL RINGING)

17:31.458 --> 17:34.166
-Kevin Bacon!
-(BANGING ON DOOR)

17:34.250 --> 17:39.083
Okay, guys, I don't know what
you're thinking, but this is not cool.

17:39.166 --> 17:40.291
This is private property.

17:40.416 --> 17:46.291
Now, kindly put down my elf
and my candy cane and go.

17:46.625 --> 17:48.583
I'm calling the police right now.

17:51.416 --> 17:52.708
(GASPS)

17:53.583 --> 17:55.500
OPERATOR OVER PHONE:
911. What's your emergency?

17:55.708 --> 17:57.791
You're coming with us.
As a Christmas present.

17:57.875 --> 18:01.208
911. Can I help you? Hello? Hello?

18:01.791 --> 18:04.708
There's two... I don't know what they are.
People in costumes.

18:04.791 --> 18:05.916
(GASPS)

18:06.000 --> 18:08.583
MAN: (SINGING)
I want an alien for Christmas

18:08.666 --> 18:12.125
Bring me an alien this year

18:12.208 --> 18:15.708
I want a little green guy
About three feet high...

18:15.833 --> 18:18.000
(SCREECHING)

18:18.375 --> 18:23.083
I want an alien for Christmas
this year

18:42.750 --> 18:43.958
-DRAX: Wait.
-What?

18:44.041 --> 18:45.875
I left my little funny man
back in the house.

18:46.083 --> 18:47.375
-What?
-I wanna go back and get him.

18:47.458 --> 18:49.250
But Kevin Bacon is gonna get away.

18:49.333 --> 18:51.333
But you still have your swirly
red and white curly man.

18:51.416 --> 18:54.125
How can you possibly think this is a man?

18:54.500 --> 18:57.958
-What is it?
-I don't know. A shape?

18:58.083 --> 19:00.541
Well, how is it fair you get to keep it
and I don't?

19:00.625 --> 19:03.250
Because I was responsible
and held on to it.

19:05.083 --> 19:08.708
Drax, do you love Peter
and want to save Christmas?

19:08.833 --> 19:10.625
Or do you want a little funny man?

19:11.833 --> 19:13.333
Uh...

19:18.166 --> 19:20.375
-A little funny man.
-No!

19:22.500 --> 19:23.750
(SIGHS)

19:31.125 --> 19:33.625
(MANTIS SNARLING)

19:36.000 --> 19:37.791
(SIREN WAILING)

19:44.041 --> 19:48.500
-Mr. Bacon. We got your 911 call.
-You gotta get these things away from me.

19:50.458 --> 19:52.166
Hey, I'm a police officer.

19:52.250 --> 19:55.208
I don't know what's going on here,
but you need to back up or I'll shoot.

19:55.500 --> 19:58.375
Raise your hands above your head! Stop!

19:58.500 --> 20:00.125
-(GUN FIRES)
-(DRAX CHUCKLES)

20:01.708 --> 20:03.416
(LAUGHS)

20:04.166 --> 20:08.041
Stop. It tickles.
Stop. I'm gonna pee my pants.

20:08.125 --> 20:09.625
(DRAX LAUGHING)

20:14.541 --> 20:16.791
-Sleep.
-Hey!

20:20.125 --> 20:21.666
-Sleep.
-Let him go! Let him go! Let him go!

20:21.750 --> 20:24.000
Freeze! Get on the ground!
Get on the ground!

20:32.750 --> 20:33.750
Sleep.

20:36.375 --> 20:38.041
(SIREN WAILING)

20:41.333 --> 20:42.708
(DRAX LAUGHS HEARTILY)

20:46.708 --> 20:49.708
Drax! You can't just kill people.

20:49.791 --> 20:52.166
Well, how am I supposed to know the rules
if no one tells me?

21:03.500 --> 21:04.666
Are you okay?

21:06.208 --> 21:08.083
We are not doing anything wrong.

21:08.500 --> 21:11.583
We are just taking the legendary hero
Kevin Bacon,

21:11.666 --> 21:14.916
to give him as a present to a friend
who is sad about Christmas.

21:15.166 --> 21:16.166
Okay.

21:19.125 --> 21:20.125
Here.

21:24.583 --> 21:28.541
I really wanted this,
but we're even now, okay?

21:30.250 --> 21:31.250
Sure.

21:32.666 --> 21:35.708
That doesn't look like a man to you,
does it?

21:35.833 --> 21:38.291
A man? No.

21:39.375 --> 21:42.875
Of course not.
My friend is being an idiot.

21:45.625 --> 21:47.208
(PANTING)

21:49.125 --> 21:50.208
(GASPS)

21:51.083 --> 21:52.791
You would love to come with us.

21:54.250 --> 21:58.333
-Hey, where are we going?
-First, there.

22:00.375 --> 22:01.500
Whoa!

22:01.583 --> 22:02.583
Coolness.

22:03.375 --> 22:04.791
CHORUS: (SINGING)
Shoo bop, shoo bop

22:04.916 --> 22:06.625
Sha la la la la

22:07.250 --> 22:08.916
Shoo bop, shoo bop

22:09.166 --> 22:12.625
WOMAN: I ain't got no time for it now
Oh, no, no

22:12.791 --> 22:15.875
I got to make this holiday glow

22:15.958 --> 22:16.958
CHORUS:
Like a lightbulb

22:17.041 --> 22:18.791
Are you friends with the Fonz?

22:19.375 --> 22:21.166
-Who?
-The Fonz.

22:21.541 --> 22:25.333
-Fonz. He's a hero, like you.
-Have the two of you ever had a team-up?

22:25.416 --> 22:27.791
Oh. Well, the Fonz's real name
is Henry Winkler.

22:27.875 --> 22:30.291
And, yeah, I do know him.
He's a very nice guy.

22:30.458 --> 22:33.833
Would you consider grabbing dinner,
like, one time a team-up?

22:33.916 --> 22:36.916
No. Eating together is not a team-up.

22:37.041 --> 22:39.250
Tell us, what was it like
when you had to save a small town

22:39.333 --> 22:40.500
by dancing like an idiot?

22:40.916 --> 22:42.666
Oh. Well, that wasn't me.

22:42.750 --> 22:46.833
That was a character that I played,
Ren McCormack, in the movie, Footloose.

22:47.083 --> 22:48.083
What?

22:48.291 --> 22:50.250
What about when you fought and defeated

22:50.333 --> 22:54.000
the super-strong masked killer
Jason Voorhees in the woods?

22:54.166 --> 22:55.166
Yeah.

22:55.958 --> 22:58.458
Nope. Again, not me.
Just a character I played.

22:58.791 --> 23:01.333
And he didn't actually kill Jason.

23:01.625 --> 23:05.083
He got stabbed through the neck
with an arrow.

23:05.166 --> 23:06.458
(LAUGHS)

23:07.541 --> 23:08.541
Yeah.

23:12.291 --> 23:16.041
He's an actor!
He's never actually saved anyone.

23:16.166 --> 23:18.583
-But actors are repugnant.
-I know.

23:18.666 --> 23:20.541
(RETCHING AND COUGHING)

23:21.250 --> 23:24.000
They make me feel gross and creepy
when they pretend to be someone else.

23:24.083 --> 23:26.875
(CHUCKLES) No.
Acting is a wonderful profession.

23:26.958 --> 23:29.000
I mean, you don't get to live
just one life,

23:29.083 --> 23:30.500
you get to live so many lives...

23:30.583 --> 23:35.083
(GROANS) We got Quill the worst gift ever.
A disgusting actor!

23:35.958 --> 23:40.916
-This is the worst day of my life!
-We ruined Christmas worse than Yondu.

23:41.208 --> 23:45.083
Peter was a child when he left Earth.
His memory is all screwed up.

23:45.375 --> 23:47.041
He doesn't remember things right.

23:49.875 --> 23:53.333
Kevin Bacon, you have to pretend
you're an actual hero,

23:53.416 --> 23:55.666
or else Christmas is doomed.

23:57.541 --> 23:58.916
(IN BRITISH ACCENT) Blimey, mate.

23:59.000 --> 24:01.791
I can't wait to storm them Nazis
on the beach.

24:02.416 --> 24:05.083
-What are you doing?
-I'm a hero, ain't I then?

24:05.166 --> 24:08.250
I'm a private in the British Army
during World War II.

24:08.333 --> 24:10.583
No. Just your regular voice.

24:10.666 --> 24:14.666
(IN NORMAL ACCENT) Oh. Okay.
Yeah, sure, fine. Hello. I'm the Batman.

24:15.250 --> 24:19.000
-I mean, hello. I'm Bruce Wayne.
-Who is Bruce Wayne?

24:19.125 --> 24:23.125
No! Don't be someone else. Be Kevin Bacon,
but, like, if you didn't suck!

24:23.250 --> 24:25.541
(LAUGHS)

24:27.041 --> 24:28.208
That's something.

24:29.125 --> 24:33.500
How weird. 'Cause, like, normally,
it would really piss me off,

24:33.583 --> 24:34.583
but I don't know.

24:34.791 --> 24:41.291
Right now, for some reason,
I just feel really great about all of it.

24:42.208 --> 24:43.500
Hmm.

24:44.041 --> 24:45.083
We hate you.

24:58.833 --> 25:02.083
MAN: (SINGING)
We watch the children playing

25:03.500 --> 25:06.333
Beside the Christmas tree

25:09.000 --> 25:13.000
Presents are wrapped up
It's beautiful

25:13.541 --> 25:19.708
And secretly the gifts you hide

25:20.541 --> 25:26.458
The fun awaits for you inside

25:27.625 --> 25:30.958
Christmastime has come

25:32.125 --> 25:35.250
There'll be toys for everyone

25:36.875 --> 25:42.583
'Cause Christmastime has come for you

25:42.750 --> 25:45.083
I remember dreaming

25:46.250 --> 25:52.458
-Wishing, hoping, praying for this day
-(MOUTHING)

25:52.541 --> 25:54.125
Now I sit and watch them

25:55.250 --> 25:58.333
The little ones I love

25:59.666 --> 26:03.708
So excited by the way

26:05.125 --> 26:08.833
Christmastime has come

26:09.333 --> 26:12.875
There'll be toys for everyone

26:14.166 --> 26:20.250
'Cause Christmastime has come for you

26:30.166 --> 26:32.833
And now the word is given

26:34.250 --> 26:36.958
It's time to peer inside

26:39.708 --> 26:41.000
Are you kidding me?

26:41.833 --> 26:46.750
So anxious for your look of joy

26:47.041 --> 26:52.416
Merry Christmas, Peter.
From me and Drax and, you know,

26:55.458 --> 26:56.625
all of us, really.

26:59.375 --> 27:01.750
Christmastime has come

27:02.500 --> 27:05.666
There'll be toys for everyone

27:07.750 --> 27:13.083
'Cause Christmastime has come

27:14.291 --> 27:16.125
For you

27:18.625 --> 27:20.791
Oh! You guys.

27:21.625 --> 27:25.083
There'll be toys for everyone

27:26.750 --> 27:27.875
What did you do?

27:27.958 --> 27:30.708
'Cause Christmastime has come

27:30.791 --> 27:33.083
For you

27:35.833 --> 27:37.666
(BOX THUMPING)

27:41.708 --> 27:44.750
KEVIN: Hey, uh, guys,
I'm about to pass out.

27:44.833 --> 27:46.333
There's no air in here.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.583
(MANTIS GIGGLES)

27:58.041 --> 27:59.125
Ta-da!

27:59.333 --> 28:02.500
You must be Pete. Merry Christmas!

28:03.791 --> 28:07.333
It's Kevin Bacon. He's not a loser.
He's great. We don't hate him at all.

28:09.583 --> 28:10.583
What'd you do?

28:10.666 --> 28:12.291
-What?
-What did you do?

28:12.458 --> 28:16.791
-We got you Kevin Bacon as a present.
-You got me a human being as a present?

28:16.875 --> 28:18.958
What better gift for the guy
who has everything

28:19.041 --> 28:21.583
than an actual human living person?

28:21.666 --> 28:25.625
This isn't a Christmas gift!
This is human trafficking!

28:25.708 --> 28:28.333
-Yes!
-It was mostly Drax's idea.

28:28.541 --> 28:29.541
It was.

28:29.625 --> 28:31.208
Hey, Pete, I got to stick up
for these guys,

28:31.291 --> 28:33.166
because to tell you the truth,

28:33.250 --> 28:36.458
I am totally stoked
about the whole thing, man.

28:38.625 --> 28:42.291
-You used your powers on him, didn't you?
-Maybe. I can't remember.

28:42.375 --> 28:45.083
Get Kevin Bacon out of the trance now!

28:49.208 --> 28:50.833
Just be what you really are.

28:58.375 --> 28:59.833
-(SCREAMS)
-(GASPS)

29:01.250 --> 29:03.375
(SCREAMING)

29:03.500 --> 29:05.875
Dude, calm down. We're not gonna hurt you.

29:06.375 --> 29:09.791
-That's a talking raccoon.
-I'll kill you. Don't ever call me that!

29:09.875 --> 29:11.208
Whoa!

29:11.291 --> 29:13.125
Sir, sir, sir. Right here, right here.

29:13.583 --> 29:17.250
Kraglin, prepare The Bowie
for his transport back to Earth.

29:17.333 --> 29:19.208
-Aye, Captain.
-Mr. Bacon, I am so sorry.

29:19.375 --> 29:20.375
This is really embarrassing.

29:20.458 --> 29:23.083
I know you're worried sick
and your family is, too.

29:23.166 --> 29:24.958
We're gonna get you back home immediately.

29:25.041 --> 29:26.166
I am Groot.

29:26.250 --> 29:28.833
Oh. Suddenly you thought
it was a bad idea all along?

29:28.916 --> 29:29.916
I am Groot.

29:30.000 --> 29:32.500
Dude, I literally just saw you
wheel him out in front of everybody.

29:35.250 --> 29:38.333
I'm gonna let you go, Kevin Bacon.
Don't run.

29:38.958 --> 29:41.125
-You're not gonna run?
-No, no. No, no, no.

29:41.791 --> 29:43.041
(SHOUTS IN FEAR)

29:44.875 --> 29:47.458
-Go get Kevin Bacon.
-I've got it.

29:48.416 --> 29:51.500
-Don't kill him.
-NEBULA: You can't outrun me, Bacon!

30:03.041 --> 30:04.666
Hey, that man was a plant.

30:04.750 --> 30:08.625
Oh, Groot? He's just a kid.
Sorry about all this stuff.

30:09.166 --> 30:10.708
What's that on your head?

30:11.500 --> 30:14.958
That is a device for
controlling a flying arrow.

30:15.041 --> 30:17.333
But I ain't quite got the hang of it yet.

30:19.083 --> 30:20.708
I know this must all be a shock to you,

30:20.791 --> 30:25.083
but it's only 'cause you mean a great deal
to Pete that they've done it.

30:26.708 --> 30:28.291
Pete didn't have much to love growing up,

30:28.375 --> 30:32.041
but one thing he did love
was telling us all stories about you.

30:32.333 --> 30:36.000
-Me?
-You saved a town through dancing.

30:36.916 --> 30:41.708
And once, Pete saved the whole galaxy
with dancing. For real.

30:42.250 --> 30:43.958
You taught him how to be a hero,

30:44.958 --> 30:47.250
and now he might just be
the greatest hero alive.

30:52.250 --> 30:53.416
Mant and these dopes,

30:53.500 --> 30:58.625
they was just hoping you'd bring the joy
of Christmas back into his heart, is all.

